A: Property Register  This register describes the land and estate comprised in the title. Except as mentioned below, the title includes any legal easements granted by the registered lease but is subject to any rights that it reserves, so far as those easements and rights exist and benefit or affect the registered land.  HILLINGDON 1   (17.03.2004) The Leasehold land shown edged with red on the plan of the above Title filed at the Registry and being The common parts of 26 to 60 (even) Fairfield Road, Uxbridge (UB8 1AL). NOTE 1: As to the part edged in blue on the title plan Flats 26 to 60 (even) are excluded from the title. NOTE 2: The land tinted green on the title plan is excluded from the title. 2   (17.03.2004) Short particulars of the lease(s) (or under-lease(s)) under which the land is held: Date   : 19 February 2004 Term   : from 19 February 2004 to 24 December 2163 Parties   : (1) Royle Estates (Hoddesdon) Limited (2) Fairfield Place (Uxbridge) Management Company Limited NOTE: The original Lease dated 28 April 1975 referred to in the above lease was formerly registered under title number NGL260934 3   (17.03.2004) There are excepted from the effect of registration all estates, rights, interests, powers and remedies arising upon, or by reason of, any dealing made in breach of the prohibition or restriction against dealings therewith inter vivos contained in the Lease. 4   (17.03.2004) The landlord's title is registered. 5   Unless otherwise mentioned the title includes any legal easements granted by the registered lease(s) but is subject to any rights that it reserves, so far as those easements and rights exist and benefit or affect the registered land.  1 of 5
B: Proprietorship Register  This register specifies the class of title and identifies the owner. It contains any entries that affect the right of disposal.  Title absolute  1   (17.03.2004) PROPRIETOR: FAIRFIELD PLACE (UXBRIDGE) MANAGEMENT COMPANY LIMITED (Co. Regn. No. 1205835) of 64a High Street, Hoddesdon, Herts and Fairfield Road, Uxbridge, Middlesex UB8 1AL.  C: Charges Register  This register contains any charges and other matters that affect the land.  1   (17.03.2004) A Conveyance of the freehold estate in the land tinted pink on the filed plan and other land dated 27 November 1868 made between (1) Thomas Coath and (2) William Wills contains covenants details of which are set out in the schedule of restrictive covenants hereto. 2   (17.03.2004) A Conveyance of the freehold estate in the land tinted blue on the filed plan and other land dated 15 January 1869 made between (1) Thomas Coath (2) John Henry Raffety and (3) William Wills contains covenants details of which are set out in the schedule of restrictive covenants hereto. 3   (17.03.2004) The land is subject, during the terms created by the leases of easements specified in the schedule of leases of easements hereto, to the rights granted by the said leases.  Schedule of restrictive covenants  1   The following are details of the covenants contained in the Conveyance dated 27 November 1868 referred to in the Charges Register:- "AND the said William Wills doth hereby for himself his heirs executors administrators and assigns covenant with the said Thomas Croath his heirs and assigns that he the said William Wills his heirs and assigns will keep observe and perform the said stipulations of sale hereinbefore recited or referred to so far as the same respectively relate to the use and enjoyment of the said two several pieces or parcels of land hereinbefore mentioned to be hereby granted and conveyed or intended so to be   That the respective Purchasers should within three calendar months from the eleventh day of November instant make and afterwards maintain good and sufficient fences on the side or sides of their respective lots as shown on the said plan which fences should not be more than eight feet high.   That no building on the several lots should be erected nearer to the road or roads in front than the building line shown on the said plan and which as to the said lots 18 and 19 is set back twenty feet from the south west front against Pages Lane. That there should not be erected on either of the said lots (except on Lots 14 and 53) more than two houses and not on either of the same lots 14 and 53 more than four houses and no house to be erected should be used as a tavern public house beer shop or as a shop of any description.   That the sale of beer should not be allowed on any lot.   That no bricks should be made or burnt or brick kiln used on any lot.   That no house to be erected on any of the lots 1 to 3 inclusive should be of less value than five hundred pounds on any of the lots 18 to 24 inclusive of less value than five hundred pounds on any of the lots 4 to 17 inclusive of less value than four hundred pounds on any of the lots 25 to 31 inclusive of less value than four hundred pounds on any of the said lots 32 to 59 inclusive of less value than three hundred and fifty pounds or on any of the lots 60 to 76 inclusive of less value than three hundred pounds.   The value of a building to be the amount of its net first cost in material and labour of construction only but these stipulations were not to preclude the purchaser from building stables or appurtenances to the principal house on any adjoining Lot". NOTE 1: The land tinted pink on the filed plan forms part of Lots 18  Title number AGL126670  2 of 5
